post_text: Southwest Dubois County School Corporation is pleased to announce that through a grant from the USDA, starting Monday September 14, all students who are attending school in person will receive free breakfast and lunch. The grant runs through December 31st or until the grant money runs out whichever comes first. The grant does not cover adult meals or a-la-carte items. The menu choices WILL NOT CHANGE. Current money will remain in student accounts to be used for a-al-carte items or to be used after the grant funding is exhausted, when normal pricing will resume.

post_text: Have you ever thought of having a job where you are on the same schedule as your student? Done with work by 2:00, off on the weekends, off on holidays and during the summer. Southridge High School has a food service position open for the 2019-2020 school year. 29.5 hours per week; 7:30 to 1:30 four days a week and 7:30 to 1:00 one day a week to equal 29.5. Need to be able to lift 40 pounds and stand for long periods of time. Person will also need to know how to operate a computer. For further information contact Ora Lee at 812-608-0597 or cottono@swdubois.k12.in.us You can also contact Desiree’ Hartwick at 812-630-4097. Huntingburg - Kiwanis
May 13, 2019 at 11:50 AM ·

The Huntingburg Kiwanis are proud supporters of the youth in our community!

Recently, Huntingburg Kiwanis members Mandy Allen of German American Bank and Sara Schroeder of the Huntingburg Chamber of Commerce presented a check to Xavier Horton during a special moment at Southridge Middle School.

Xavier received a check for $500 to go towards his Eagle Scout project at Freedom Reins Therapeutic Riding Center. He is building a therapy room for the children that receive services through Freedom Reins. Good job Xavier on being an active member of your community!
